<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Ericcrown</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I am extremely suprised no one else has tryed to make studded tunics. I guess I'm the only one who did. I did as the tailoring book stated: I used 1 medium quality cat pelt, 1 tunic pattern, and 5 studds. I cobine them all in a large sewing kit and I get the messege "Those items do not combine in those quantities to form anything." I have complained neumorous times to everquest and still no fix. Not only that but they told me the first 5 messeges I sent that I was doing it wrong and should find the book on tailoring. HELLO??!!! I have that. My tailoring skill is up to a 35 and let me tell you it took an enourmous amount of patience and money to get it there. My smithing is up to 50 just to make the studs. So please, spread the word that you cant make this item. It will save alot of people time and money. I hope to be the best tailor on the Terew Marr server. I know tailoring is the hardest skill out of all of them and it pays very little but I want to be able to offer good armor to monks and druids. I hope to succeed where no one else has. Wish me luck.<P>Ericcrown High Elf Cleric of Tarew Marr<BR>Level 21</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Glane</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I haven't tried making any studded tunics, because I have read that they are currently not working: <A HREF="http://eq.stratics.com/gamersforum/tradeskills.html" TARGET=_blank>http://eq.stratics.com/gamersforum/tradeskills.html</A>   I have ready several posts on other message boards saying the same thing.  Your quantities are correct.  This is not acceptable and severely cripples our trade.  I am not sure why this hasn't been corrected yet, but I will continue to contact them everyday.<P>Human Bard of Quellious<BR>Level 11</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Blubberbuster</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Are you stacking the studs ? or placing them seperately ? when multiple objects are normally asked for in the game, I find that you normally have to place 1 in a seperate slot .. stacking does not work...<P>Just an Idea .. like to know your results .<P>Blubberbuster(TZ)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Aikibu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Studs are a non-stackable item.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Ziglar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Yes you can make studded tunics I have made one early on before I gave up that trade for smithing. You must not stack the items when you combine. Sorry to say I was on Rallos Zek and gave it to a friend who lost it to a PK  <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/frown.gif"> never tried to make another but it is possible  <IMG SRC="http://www.everlore.com/boards/EL/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Hippun</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Uhh im pretty sure you have to be excellent at tailoring to make studded leather. meaning you need at least 100 im sure. get to 100 and THEN complain if if you cant.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Graba Jenwu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Like some of you, I want to excel at one of the toughest skill in the game.  Someone out there can benefit from tailoring.  Alhtough it is VERY frustrating, it takes quite a bit of time to be successful.  I have found East and West Commons to be the best source of Medium Quality pelts for Studded.  I made PW Armor up to skill level 22.  Then I started to attempt studded.  I failed quite a bit, but my skill has increased beyond 25.  I have made about 4 items.  Keep on sewing.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Haldir Denethorn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">In reply to Hippun :<P>At skill 26 Patchwork becomes trivial, and after that you have to start making studded. You're probably mistaking it for Reinforced Leather, where a reasonable starting skill is about 90. Studded masks (now that the pattern is in) can be made from about 20.<P>Second, if the message the person got is "The items did not combine in those quantities to make anything", it's not the same as "You lack the skill to craft the item". So it is clearly not because the person has too low skill, it's the proportions that are wrong. And since multiple people have verified the proportions were correct, either in the Tailoring book or on web sites, then it is obvious that this item cannot be made because of a bug.<P>Haldir</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Meran</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">What does the pw other than gorget do for stat bonuses? Thanks.<BR>Meran</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
